          <b>Sanderstead Residents' Association AGM  14th May 2015</b>

<p>The Chairman Dennis King welcomed over 50 members of the SRA to the AGM which was also attended by Councillors Maria Gatland, Yvette Hopley and Tim Pollard.</p>

<p>Mike Leach, the Hon Secretary, in his report  highlighted the year's planning applications, where the Lidl scheme at Hamsey Green had on Appeal had been refused by the Planning Inspector, the demolition of two houses in Purley Downs Road  to be replaced with flats had also been refused, but there was concern that the new Labour Council controlled Planning Committee was approving back land development which had been previously refused. Three new notice boards are to replace the existing at Sanderstead and Hamsey Green.</p>

<p>John Kempsell, the Hon Treasurer reported on the Associations accounts which made a small surplus for 2014. Grants of £2700 had been made to local organisations in 2014 with a further £2975 to be presented later at the AGM.</p>

<p>All the Officers were re-elected with the welcome addition of new member Corrie Hibberd in the special capacity of Webmaster for the Association’s Website.</p>

</p>The enjoyable part of the Association’s AGM is always the presentation of grants to the various local organisations, particularly the uniformed youth groups.</p>

</p>A reward of a £25 voucher is always made to youngsters who write an article for the Sanderstead News.<p>
