<b>Hear Me Speak</b>
<p>Cliff Quartly reported on "Hear Me Speak" the SRA sponsored competition for year 6 primary school children to give them confidence in public speaking. In 2014 three schools entered the competition which proved such a success that this year five schools will be entering teams this year.</p>

<p>The competition this year will be held at Gresham Primary School who will be presented with the new SRA "Hear Me Speak" Shield as last year's winners. The question is will they be able to retain it for the coming year? </p>

<p>The date for this year's competition is 18th June and should you wish to attend please contact Cliff Quartly, 020 8651 1164</p>

<b>The SRA Website</b>

<p>Corrie Hibberd demonstrated the website that she has designed for the SRA. The quality, ease of access and local Sanderstead information on its organisations and events impressed the members who applauded its author.</p>

<p>The Chairman thanked everybody for attending on such a wet evening, also the  Committee for their work over the year and his wife Maureen for her support.</p>

<p>The meeting concluded with refreshment. </p>    

